text: Robert Warner (fl. 1390), of Marlborough, Wiltshire, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Marlborough in January 1390. In 1388–89, he was Mayor of Marlborough. ==References== Category:Year of birth missing Category:Year of death missing Category:English MPs January 1390 Category:People from Marlborough, Wiltshire
